The paper discusses reinforcement learning (RL) and recurrent neural networks (RNNs) in the context of learning to think and plan abstractly. This suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the machine learning (cs.LG), artificial intelligence (cs.AI), and neural and evolutionary computing (cs.NE) sub-categories. Additionally, the paper mentions driving simulated cars, which suggests that it may also belong to the robotics (cs.RO) sub-category. Finally, the paper discusses the RNNAI's ability to learn from never-ending sequences of tasks, which suggests that it may also belong to the systems and control (cs.SY) sub-category.
